Content: "Transfer learning enables models pre-trained on large general corpora to adapt to specialized tasks with minimal fine-tuning data. The frozen lower layers retain universal feature representations while the upper layers are retrained on domain-specific examples. LoRA and QLoRA reduce memory requirements by decomposing weight updates into low-rank matrices, achieving comparable performance to full fine-tuning with 10-100x fewer trainable parameters. The choice of rank (typically 4-64) trades off between adaptation capacity and regularization."

